review_text:
A OK 3 stars for easily depositing a check for rent that we brought over with a cashier check from Wells Fargo into a M&T bank account. No other customers were here when we were here. 

Outside parking with some one way angled parking. 

Drive thru bank services must be nice for those extreme weather days.

I had a issue closing my account from a different state.
Mr. Vernon was very understanding, was very professional and took his time to correct the issue and after quite a few weeks of tussle, closed the account and made me a happier individual. At first I was very upset and very hard to deal with but Mr. Vernon is the go to guy. He saved the day and my sanity. Otherwise Its a great local bank. Thank you all. Hope this helps.

To me, most financial institution branches are cookie cutter-esque.  What sets this M&T branch apart from others that I've frequented is the wonderful customer service that I consistently receive while banking inside.  It more than makes up for the somewhat confusing parking lot that can tend to be an issue for some people.  That, my friends, is M&T Bank - located at the corner or Rte. 52 and Jackson St. - in a nutshell.
